# WhatsApp Call Setup with VAPI AI

## Overview
This setup allows users to call your WhatsApp number and have VAPI AI answer the call.

## Files Created
- `supabase/functions/whatsapp-call-webhook/index.ts` - Handles incoming WhatsApp calls
- `supabase/migrations/20260420120000_whatsapp_calls_table.sql` - Database table

## Setup Steps

### 1. Link Supabase Project (if not already linked)

```bash
cd "C:\Users\Mohammed Shishir\OneDrive\Desktop\websites\lunexo media com"
npx supabase link
```

Enter your project URL when prompted (e.g., `https://xxxxx.supabase.co`)

### 2. Create Database Table

Run the migration:
```bash
npx supabase db push
```

Or run this SQL in Supabase SQL Editor:
```sql
CREATE TABLE public.whatsapp_calls (
  id UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  call_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  from_number TEXT NOT NULL,
  to_number TEXT NOT NULL,
  status TEXT,
  event TEXT,
  vapi_call_id TEXT,
  vapi_status TEXT,
  accepted_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  connected_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  failed_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  duration_seconds INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  failure_reason TEXT,
  metadata JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
CREATE INDEX idx_whatsapp_calls_call_id ON whatsapp_calls(call_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_whatsapp_calls_from_number ON whatsapp_calls(from_number);
CREATE INDEX idx_whatsapp_calls_created_at ON whatsapp_calls(created_at DESC);
```

### 3. Deploy Supabase Function

```bash
npx supabase functions deploy whatsapp-call-webhook
```

### 4. Set Supabase Secrets

```bash
npx supabase functions secrets set whatsapp-call-webhook \
  VAPI_API_KEY=your_vapi_api_key \
  VAPI_WORKFLOW_ID=your_vapi_workflow_id
```

### 5. Configure WhatsApp Webhook

In Meta Developers Dashboard → WhatsApp → Configuration:
- Callback URL: `https://your-project.supabase.co/functions/v1/whatsapp-call-webhook`
- Verify Token: `lunexo_verify_123`
- Subscribe to: `calls` event

### 6. VAPI Setup

1. Go to https://vapi.ai
2. Create a Workflow/Assistant for your use case
3. Configure AI personality and instructions
4. Get Workflow ID from settings
5. Get API Key from account settings

## How It Works

1. User calls your WhatsApp number
2. WhatsApp sends `ring` event to webhook
3. Webhook saves call to database
4. Webhook triggers VAPI to connect
5. VAPI AI answers and handles conversation
6. All call events are tracked in database

## Testing

After setup, call your WhatsApp number - VAPI AI should answer!
